AGI - Two international crises that are revolutionizing world balances, protests in universities and a diplomatic case. Sergio Mattarella landed in New York for a visit that will see him intervened at the General Assembly of the UN, fourth head of the State of Republican history, and the agenda is tied to every passing hour. Unity and dialogue without prevarication, will be the President's leitmotiv, I am the only instrument to overcome the crises that risk to precipitate the world into a total war, while the UN, whose function remains decisive, however, needs a reform, in particular for what concerns the Security Council, remained linked to a "geographical map" exceeded.
&nbsp;
Multilateralism is the key point of the head of the state, it is the only way to avoid new conflicts, but it serves that reform of the United Nations invoked for decades. Just consider that two of the three predecessors of Mattarella, Oscar Luigi Scalfaro and Giorgio Napolitano, in their interventions at the UN had to ask for a new model of governance faster and more effective. But next to this there will be room for the two crisis, the Ukrainian and Gaza crisis. While the latter is fueling student protests at many universities in the United States, so much so that the prestigious New York Columbia university, where Mattarella should meet the leadership of the Italian Academy, is still closed to the outside after the eviction a few days ago that fueled not little debate. During the visit, all focused on the UN, there is no meeting with the White House, where Mattarella was visiting in 2016 (with Obama) and 2019 (with Trump), while with Joe Biden the last interview, in Italy, dates back to 2021.
&nbsp;
But the diplomats of the two countries are certainly in contact, in these hours, also for the increase of polemics for the story of the Italian student, Matteo Falcinelli, arrested and abused by the Miami police. The first commitment, today, will be the intervention at the Conference on the implementation status of Objective 16 of Agenda 2030, 'Peace, justice and institutions for sustainable development', then an interview with Secretary General Antonio Guterres is planned. Tuesday, May 7th; Mattarella will be at the General Assembly, for a speech on "Italy, United Nations and multilateralism to address the common challenges"

